 it to tiny provenance fields and keep `record_hash` for raw-line correlation.\\n\\n- **P2: Mixed content can leave copied text/tool payloads inside `source_record`.**  \\n  Codex pruning only removes copied message content when the payload is â€śplain textâ€ť at [transcript.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/transcript.rs:270); Claude pruning similarly preserves mixed content around [transcript.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/transcript.rs:448). That matches the docs, but it means mixed provider records can still store raw text or tool input under non-sensitive keys, where `redact_text` misses low-entropy secrets and paths. POC-sized fix: prefer deleting the whole copied content/input/output field once normalized fields are extracted, even if that loses mixed sibling data, or add a focused mixed-content privacy test before keeping this behavior.\\n\\nNo edits made; I did not run tests.\"}}","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-11T17:54:25.388Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}